===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|explosionis|explōsiōnis|lang=la}}, genitive form of {{term|explosio|explōsio|lang=la}}, from {{term|explodo|explōdo|I drive out by clapping|lang=la}}, from {{term|ex-|lang=la}} and {{term|plodo|plōdo|I clap or strike|lang=la}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/ɪkˈspləʊ.ʒən/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ɛkˈsploʊ.ʒən/}}
* {{audio|en-us-explosion.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[violent]] release of [[energy]] (sometimes [[mechanical]], [[nuclear]], or [[chemical]].)
# A [[burst]]ing due to [[pressure]].
# The [[sound]] of an explosion.
# A sudden uncontrolled [[increase]].
#* {{RQ:Schuster Hepaticae V|3-4}}
#*: As with the Lejeuneaceae, this pattern of massive speciation appears to be correlated with the Cretaceous '''explosion''' of the angiosperms and the simultaneous creation of a host of new microenvironments, differing in humidity, light intensity, texture, etc.
# A sudden [[outburst]].

